.TH sndr 4 "08 Jun 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
sndr \- SNDR parameter values
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fB/etc/default/sndr\fR
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The
.B sndr
file resides in \fB/etc/default\fR and provides startup
parameters for the
.BR sndrd "(1M) and"
.BR sndrsyncd (1M)
daemons.
.sp
.LP
The
.B sndr
file format is ASCII and comment lines begin with the
crosshatch (#)  character. Parameters consist of a keyword followed by an
equal (=) sign  followed by the parameter value of the form:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
keyword=value
.fi
.in -2

.sp
.LP
The following parameters are currently supported in the
.B sndr
file:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SNDR_THREADS=num
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Sets the maximum number of connections allowed to the server over
connection-oriented transports.  By default, the number of connections is
16.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SNDR_LISTEN_BACKLOG=num
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Sets connection queue length for the RDC TCP over a connection-oriented
transport. The default value is 10 entries.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SNDR_TRANSPORT=string
.ad
.sp .6
.RS 4n
Sets the transport used for the RDC connection. If IPv6 is installed, the
default value is "\fB/dev/tcp\fR" or "\fB/dev/tcp6\fR."
.RE

